## Model-Specific Prompting Differences (2026)

Frontier models have diverged in how they respond to prompt structure. Apply these differences when
optimizing for a specific target platform:

| Model | Preferred Style | Key Notes |
|---|---|---|
| **Claude Opus 4+** | XML tags, modular sections, conversational tone | Responds well to structured context blocks; aggressive caps degrade output; sweet spot ~150–300 words |
| **GPT-5 series** | Markdown headers, scratchpad `<thinking>` tags for o-series | Router architecture handles reasoning internally; pin to model snapshots in production; try zero-shot first |
| **Gemini 2.5+** | Short, direct prompts; few-shot examples; data/tables | Prefers examples over instructions; place specific questions after context data; 1M+ context window makes placement critical |

When the target model is unspecified, produce a model-agnostic prompt and note where divergence matters.

